                     <interp inst="t18210411-72-person863" type="surname" value="Bell"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18210411-72-person863" type="given" value="Luke"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18210411-72-person863" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     </persName>
                  , a warrant officer, performed on board a certain ship of our late Lord the King, called the Spartan - (here the indictment set forth a similar account to that in the preceding case; one among which purports to be a receipt of 
                     <persName id="t18210411-72-person864">
                        Luke 
                        Bell
                     <interp inst="t18210411-72-person864" type="surname" value="Bell"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18210411-72-person864" type="given" value="Luke"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18210411-72-person864" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     </persName>
                  , for 2 l. 4 s. 8 d. witnessed as before. The total amount of savings, according to the certificate. was 59 l. 18 s.) - with intent to defraud our said late Lord the King
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>SEVEN OTHER COUNTS, varying the manner of laying the charges.</p>
               <p>
            
